summary = ["But many were already angry at him for what they said was his failure to articulate a clear message for the party going into the elections and for a messy budget process that gave President Clinton a political edge and contradicted Republican principles of fiscal conservativism by containing massive amounts of spending for local projects I'm hoping more people will understand the need for a serious reassessment this year,'' said Rep Charles T Canady, R-Fla, who said he had hoped for a challenge to the speaker after the 1996 elections, when the Republicans also lost seats But many were already angry at him for what they said was his failure to articulate a clear message for the party going into the elections and for a messy budget process that gave President Clinton a political edge and contradicted Republican principles of fiscal conservativism by containing massive amounts of pork spending"]